<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="preserve-vt">preserve <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /prɪ'zɜːv/    美 /prɪ'zɜːrv/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-save">1.★ <strong>保护；保存 (save)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>preserve one’s eyesight 
保护视力</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These eighteenth-century oil paintings are preserved so well that the visitors are greatly amazed. 
这些18世纪的油画保存得这么好，使参观者大为惊叹。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>preservation /ˌprezə'veɪʃn/ n [U]   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In wilderness is the preservation of the world. 
世界存留于荒野之中。</p><footer>—— 梭罗 / 2012 北京</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— The town is so beautiful! I just love it.
— Me too. The character of the town is well <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (保存).  （2013 江苏改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. preserved / saved  </p></div>